commit.message:
Fix calling wxOverlay::Reset() without Init() first under Mac

It is valid to call Reset() even if Init() had never been called, e.g.
when we didn't need to draw anything on the overlay, but it asserted and
crashed in this case because it used invalid m_overlayWindow under Mac.

Fix this by simply doing nothing in Reset() if m_overlayWindow was not
initialized.

This commit is best viewed ignoring whitespace-only changes.

Closes #24415.

Co-Authored-By: Daniel Kulp <dan@kulp.com>

Merge branch 'notif-dismiss-reason' of https://github.com/lanurmi/wxWidgets

Expose reason for notification dismissal through SetInt().

See #24340.

Fix typo in the guard checking for MAC_OS_VERSION_13_0 presence

See #24431.

Merge branch 'webkit-item-title-deprecated'

Avoid using deprecated webkit_back_forward_list_item_get_title() with
recent WebKitGTK versions.

See #24436.

Merge branch 'clipboard-fixes'

Fix copying/pasting text to/from clipboard in wxGTK under Wayland.

See #24423.

Merge branch 'locale-script-fixes'

Improve handling of the "script" part of the locale, notably fixing
zh-Hans-CN locale support under macOS.

See #24399.

Merge branch 'bmpbundle-scaling'

Fix several problems with using non-square bitmaps in wxBitmapBundle.

See #24435.

Stop using deprecated webkit_back_forward_list_item_get_title()

WebKit 2.43.4 and later deprecated this function because it doesn't do
anything any more, as the titles are not stored in the history, and just
returns an empty string.

See https://github.com/WebKit/WebKit/commit/4ef4b65d33f45734ad3c6cbc7f2fe0dda17051bc

Fix handling of sizes differing in width only in wxBitmapBundle

We assumed that bitmaps with the same height also have the same width,
but this is not necessarily true and if it did happen, GetBitmap()
failed it postcondition of returning the bitmap with the requested size.

Fix this by rescaling the closest bitmap to have the correct width even
if it already has the correct height.

Also enhance the bitmap comparator used for sorting to work correctly
with the bitmaps of the same height but different width.

Closes #24434.

Fix scale computation in wxBitmapBundle for some bitmap sizes

GetNextAvailableScale() returned wrong result when the bitmap size was
not exactly divisible by the scale, but this didn't matter for square
bitmaps because multiplying the default size by the not quite correct
scale still rounded to the correct size.

This was not the case for non-square bitmaps, however, as all our
computations use only bitmap height and dividing bitmap width by the
exact scale and multiplying it by the scale computed from the scaled and
unscaled height values could result in a value different from the
initial one, as shown by the newly added unit test, which failed before
this commit.

Fix this by computing the ratio of the bitmap to the base one and then
multiplying this ratio by the bitmap scale.

Closes #24433.

Add wxString::FromUTF8() around WebKit function calls

The strings returned by WebKit are always UTF-8-encoded, but wxString
may, in theory, use another encoding, so call FromUTF8() explicitly, as
was already done elsewhere.

Refactor wxWebViewHistoryItem creation code in wxWebViewWebKit

No real changes, just add CreateHistoryItemFromWKItem() helper to avoid
repeating the same code twice.

Merge branch 'mac-warn-fixes'

Some trivial Mac-specific warnings fixes.

See #24431.

Simplify wxrc code by removing broken support for multiple bases

This code was added back in aac18ec71e (generate ctors with optional
parent parameters in C++ code (patch 1238355), 2006-05-06) but
apparently never worked, as it generated uncompilable code if it was
executed (see #24383) and doesn't seem to make any sense as the name of
the class defined in XRC can never be "wxMenu" or any other of the
already existing wx classes.

Revert this to simplify the code.

See #7433.

Closes #24422.

Avoid unused parameter warnings in Mac wxWebViewChromium code

Don't name the "id" parameter that we don't use neither, just as we
already did for "SEL" one.

Define MAC_OS_VERSION_14_0 and other possibly missing symbols

This avoids warnings about comparing __MAC_OS_X_VERSION_MAX_ALLOWED with
MAC_OS_VERSION_14_0 in src/osx/cocoa/window.mm.

Also define the other similar symbols for consistency.

Fix uninitialized wxGLCanvasEGL Wayland members

These were left out of dbaa024467 (Initialize wxGLCanvasEGL members in
their declarations, 2024-03-15) causing crashes.

Closes #24426.

Remove implicit conversion of wxGdkAtom to GdkAtom

This made things confusing, especially due to the presence of implicit
conversions in wxDataFormat and overloaded comparison operators, so call
Get() explicitly to be more sure about what is going on.

No real changes.

Don't advertise wxDF_TEXT when copying text under Wayland

Somehow, this replaces wxDF_UNICODETEXT in the list of available formats
instead of being added to it, and it's better to provide the Unicode
text (i.e. UTF8_STRING mapped by GTK to "text/plain;charset=utf-8") than
just plain text (STRING, mapped to "text/plain") if we can't provide
both.

Accept text/plain format when pasting from clipboard in wxGTK too

Consider UTF8_STRING and "text/plain;charset=utf-8" to be equivalent
(and the same thing for STRING and "text/plain"), so that wxClipboard
can accept text from both X11 and Wayland applications when pasting.

Closes #24391.

Use wxScopedArray instead of manual memory allocation

No real changes, just simplify the code by using smart pointer class.

Define wxTextDataObject::GetAllFormats() in one place only

All ports having this function returned wxDF_UNICODETEXT and wxDF_TEXT
from it, so define it only once instead of having slightly different
versions for all of them.

This probably fixes a bug in wxX11, which incorrectly returned just a
single format from its GetAllFormats() even if GetFormatCount() returned
2 in this port too.

Rename UTF8_STRING and STRING atoms in wxGTK code

Don't call them "text" and "altText" which doesn't make much sense, but
use the names corresponding to their strings instead.

No real changes.

Allow selecting between primary and clipboard in text sample

Add a menu item to switch between using the clipboard and primary
selections.

This finally makes UsePrimarySelection() call in the sample useful,
after 25 years when it didn't do anything, since it was added back in
7e2c43b855 (...Added for primary selection to sample/text., 1999-06-10)

Fix comment and call to UsePrimarySelection() in text sample

The call actually did nothing, but the comment implied that it did, as
if the default argument to UsePrimarySelection() were "true" -- which is
not, and never has been, the case.

Reduce confusion by clarifying what's going on here and passing an
explicit argument.

Refactor clipboard selection in text sample

Factor out the call to UsePrimarySelection() and accompanying comment in
its own function.

This doesn't make much sense yet, but will allow to avoid modifying two
copies of this code and comment in the upcoming commits.

No real changes yet.

Remove clipboard sample, wxClipboard is shown in the text sample

The sample could have been useful, in theory, but didn't do anything
more or better than the text sample in practice, so just remove it.

Always post notification dismissal event on Gtk, regardless of reason

For an unknown reason, the Gtk implementation only used to post a
wxEVT_NOTIFICATION_MESSAGE_DISMISSED event if the associacted reason
code was either 1 or 2. To be consistent with with MSW, post the
event regardless of what the reason was, potentially enabling the
event for reasons ByApp and Unknown.

Expose reason for notification dismissal through SetInt()

On all platforms, except macOS, the reason why a notification was
dismissed is known. Specifically, it can be useful to distinguish whether
the notification closed because of a timeout, or a click by the user.
